{\f0\fs32\b 2. PROJECT DESCRIPTION\par}
\pard\sb200\sa200

{\f0\fs24\b 2.1 What is this Project?\par}
{\f0\fs24 This is a complete e-commerce web application that allows users to:\par
\bullet  Browse and search products\par
\bullet  Add items to shopping cart\par
\bullet  Register and login to accounts\par
\bullet  Place orders and track them\par
\bullet  Admin panel for store management\par
}

{\f0\fs24\b 2.2 Problem Statement\par}
{\f0\fs24 Traditional retail businesses need digital platforms to reach wider audiences. This project addresses the need for a scalable, cloud-based e-commerce solution that can be accessed from anywhere.\par}

{\f0\fs24\b 2.3 Proposed Solution\par}
{\f0\fs24 A three-tier web application consisting of:\par
\bullet  Presentation Layer: React.js frontend hosted on Vercel\par
\bullet  Business Logic Layer: Node.js/Express backend hosted on Azure\par
\bullet  Data Layer: MongoDB Atlas cloud database\par
}

{\f0\fs24\b 2.4 Key Features\par}
{\f0\fs24\b Customer Features:\par}
{\f0\fs24
\bullet  Product browsing with categories and search\par
\bullet  Shopping cart management\par
\bullet  User registration and authentication\par
\bullet  Order placement and history\par
\bullet  Responsive design for all devices\par
